[{"id":"VR852789","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following best represents the magnitude and direction of the momentum of the two-block system after the collision?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR852789_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Blocks <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> slide toward each other on a horizontal track, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mn>1</mn> </math></span></span>. There is negligible friction between the blocks and the track. Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> shows a momentum bar chart that represents the magnitude and direction of the momentum of each block before they collide.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown, labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2. Figure 1 shows two identical blocks, labeled from left to right Block 1 and Block 2, moving towards each other on a flat horizontal surface. Figure 2 shows two bar graphs in coordinate planes, with the origins labeled 0. The vertical axes in both graphsÂ are labeled p, and indicate that upward is positive. The first graph is labeled Block 1 and the value of the bar is positive 3 units. The second graph is labeled Block 2 and the value of the bar is negative 1 unit.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR852789.g26.svg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"></span></p>\n\n\n<span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=